author: COMSOL
description:
This application illustrates how to model an electric machine, such as a generator, motor, or drive, by exploiting its sector symmetry to reduce the size of the problem. The machine being studied is a simplified electric generator in 3D, based on the geometry used in the generator_2d application.

The application uses the Rotating Machinery, Magnetic interface. It is recommended to have a look at the model rotating_machinery_3d_tutorial before proceeding with this application.

settings.value:
Internal Rotor – Surface Mounted Magnets

This is an internal rotor part with surface mounted permanent magnets. It is developed primarily to be used together with an external stator part, in order to simulate rotating electric motors.

For more information, check the documentation in the corresponding *.pdf document.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
External Stator – Slotted

This is an external slotted stator part. It is developed primarily to be used together with an internal rotor part, in order to simulate rotating electric motors.

For more information, check the documentation in the corresponding *.pdf document.
